Poboys were all bread. Barely enough meat.

Love the foods and the vibe. Hidden gem spot
Chef was very drunk, food took hours and possibly got food poisoning from it. Would give zero stars if I could.

Spicy Chicken was okay - I think the horsey mustard threw it off for me. So that "okay" is biased. The customer service and atmosphere was pretty great and friendly.  Drinks are also reasonably priced.  Decent dive bar to watch a game on a Sunday afternoon.
If you are looking for great authentic New Orleans food this is where you want to be!!!!
Cajun mikes? More like "that bar tender was very rude"
This place is awesome! When I visited NOLA, this was my first stop - it was very fun! The food is great, the bartender is awesome and the atmosphere is perfect!! I'm glad I stopped in!
The food was delicious. And service was amazing
Nice bar good menu selction
Go see Micah and Eric! She's a little firecracker and he'll be your best friend by the end of the night. What a great find!
Good po boys n good drinks
Cool dive bar with good food
They make you feel at home. Cold beer and good food!
Small little pub... With decent food! You can tell many locals come here agreed hangout.

Hands down THE BEST hole in the wall bar/restaurant. BBQ pork po-boy is amazing.  The cook is so sweet and told is that she slow cooks the meat for 12 hours. No prepackaged frozen bs here. Amazing service. I will come here again and again!
Met some of my classmates here to get to know each other. Got kicked out even though we were good patrons and bunch of us were buying plenty of drinks. At least we know where to not find back.
Horrid. Don’t go.
Will go again
Great food! We went twice during our 3 day stay. That’s how good the food was. Try the po’boys you won’t regret. Just can’t beat the price, less than $10 and it can feed two people. Highly recommend
Truly my favorite hole in the wall. Good food, friendly staff, diversity among customers
Staff was awesome. Food was the best that we had on our trip. Will definitely frequent again when in town.
Rude bartender refused to take a Groupon, proceeded to tell me how it's a locals only bar.   I live 3 minutes down Canal St from here.   Maybe you should go back to wherever you are from.

Wow wish I could give 0 stars. Terrible experience. Obnoxious girl bartender wouldn’t give myself and 3 other female customers the time of day. I’m a bartender myself and I would never speak to anyone the way she spoke to us. Absolutely would avoid at all costs.
Local dive. Good place to shoot the hay with folks.

You're trying to figure out if you want to eat here. You do. Everyone's always talking about how great this city is, and this pub confirmed it.  Dolton was awesome. The red beans and rice was realllyy good, the poboys was great, and the gumbo was fantastic

Pretty cool place in the city, stopped by with friends for drinks on the walk back to the apartment. Will definitely be back since it's so close. Great atmosphere, staff, and customers seemed laid back.
Bad food gross bathrooms
Po boys are the best, cheap crab claws,
Loved this diamond in the rough. The food was so good and the bartender had a great personality, we felt right at home!
Small pub with awesome food good drinks low prices
Proper dive bar.
Friendly staff and very cheap beers. Don’t let the signs fool you 🤣😉
Accept LA Wallet, if the staties accept it then why not?!
Great place!
Food

Loved it! The alligator sausage and the roast beef smash was fantastic! Boudain balls were decent.  Bathroom was unbelievably tiny! 🤣  But definitely buy Captain the pup a drink, he's a local and super sweet!
Neighborhood atmosphere.  Had fried oysters that were overcooked.  Onion rings were good.  Alligator poboy was good as were the jalapeno poppers.
A local hangout.  Across Canal Street from the French Quarter, it doesn't get the noisy obnoxious tourists.  The food was great, served quickly, and hot.
Great and awesome food and people!
Its exactly what you want. Cuban was really good
Great local pub with great locals! Enjoyed the shrimp basket and the chicken wings were delicious. The locals made us feel like locals too!
Good, friendly service.  The pressed roast beef was crazy good!  Get a side of gravy.
Great prices
Love this little bar. Good bar food at a reasonable price.
Divey. Alligator sausage poboy not quite warm through. Good onion rings. Went back a day later and got a surprisingly rude bartender. Greatly improved attitude a year later. Very good oyster basket.
Loved the amount of fried oysters given but the gumbo was not really good.

Fantastic service. Don't be afraid to go in if it seems a bit scary! Everyone was friendly. The bartender was very bubbly and personable. The drinks were great and the food comes in very generous portion sizes!
Another great local bar. It can get loud and roudy. Decent pub food.

Food was great and the people here were fun.  Had the Cuban on french roll and onion rings.....excellent meat potion size and our bartender, Lindsay Parker was a blast and took amazing care of us. Yannie the cook was awesome.  I love the local atmosphere.
Wow
Loved the red beans and rice. Locals love it here. I needed some good New Orleans food and this place has it!

Food here is really good, the cochon de lait poboy is my favorite, but I recommend getting takeout or delivery. For me, this is not a comfortable place to sit and eat. Seating is limited, space is cramped, and the music is wayyy too loud. There's no way to talk over the noise and you're likely to leave with a migraine. Take your food someplace else or have them bring it you and you'll be happy.
Best poboys around. Little dive bar hole in the wall with food that is OUTSTANDING.  Can't wait to go back when were in NOLA again in December.
Where the locals  go
This place is consistent and solid. Good food, great bar staff (Jess is awesome), and atmosphere. A can’t miss. Give it a try.

Bartender was a little rude and didn't want to discuss what beers were on tap. When asked, pointed to the taps. Didn't have ingredients to fix white Russian. I ordered a Bloody Maria with extra lime and no peppers. Had lime, lemon and pickled snaps. When asked to fix a Kamikaze, had to Google it. That's fine but when she asked another patron how to spell Kamikaze, the patron made fun of us for ordering it. In a bar with only baseball on four TV's and jamming to Biz Markie, with an inexperienced and rude bartender, hardly worth pointing out. Definitely not a positive recommendation.

Interesting place. Quite the cast of characters! We had a Groupon. Food was good- typical Pub food fare. Order at the bar. It seems the bartender is also the waitress. Kind of a hole in the wall place- not many tables. No complaints.

Really nice dive bar located off the main drag.  Great variety of music played,  due to the variety of people stopping in I'm sure.  We ate here one night too and the food was really good for a dive bar.  We stopped in multiple times during our vacation because we enjoyed it!
Whatever you do do not get the cochon de lait  sandwich it's like cat food, bad suggestion from the bartender
MY FAVORITE BAR HANDS DOWN!!!
Definitely worth the visit and good food.
Great Atmosphere, Perfectly Prepared Cuban and Muffuletta Sandwiches. Must visit for a quick bite!
Very cool place to hang out while in new Orleans
Go see Dalton, he's  my favorite bartender.
Awesome! Food is amazing, atmosphere is amazing, service is amazing! I highly recommend the alligator sausage po-boy!
great neighborhood bar. try the beer& shot combo
It was going good until the roaches started crawling on the wall. But the atmosphere was very vibrant. The bartender was great and attentive to her customers.

We had a really strange experience. I’ve never gone to a restaurant and had to worry about the cook spitting in my food before. Seems like the type of bar that attracts locals, and if the staff doesn’t recognize you then they don’t want your business

We read the reviews and wanted to give it try. At first glance seemed ok. However, we waited forever to get a menu. Once we finally got a menu, the female bartender made a statement "there is only one cook and one bartender. If you are in the service industry, then you know. Other wise get the f$$$ out". Yes, I was in the industry and did it for couple years. It's not your customers' fault that you are under staffed, when all we did was ask for a menu. Then, as we proceed to look at the menu the cook gave us dirty looks because a few other people were yelling at the bartender for other statements she made. The cook must have thought I said something, when I didn't say anything. We left because we didn't want spit in our food. Terrible place and terrible service. DO NOT GO HERE!
A very friendly place.
Cajun Mike's is a little hole in the wall with a bit of charm.  The food was middle of the road, lacked presentation and weak in flavor.  Not a place I would return to.

Service was great, food was just ok. I ordered the muffaletta and it wasn't cooked all the way through so it was cold and the cheese was barely melted..very disappointed..fried shrimp was ok but waaaaay too much salt in the batter. Very very salty
Great cochon
Very friendly environment.  Fast, tastey and great lunch menu. The staff and locals makes it a must place to visit and grab a bite.
Wanted to eat. Not allowed in with my son who serves in military. The USA is shameless and repressive
Great drinks and better service!!
The shrimp po boy was excellent.
Busy but worth the experience
My hubby and I just happened to be come across this awesome little gem. We had such a good time here. Met some interesting people.  Sat outside and had a few beverages. We would definitely go back.
Best Gumbo of our trip! Love that dark rue!
Realy good shrimps and craft beer :)
Good local pub.  Get off bourbon St awhile and enjoy this one.  The food is good too!
Awesome food, great atmosphere, and good beer.
Awesome,  cheap poboys and fries,  great food and bartenders

Both my wife and I had the oyster basket. The bartender was very helpful in making our selection. The oysters were small but plentiful, some were a little over cooked for us, but they had a great flavor. There homemade remoulade and coldslaw was 5⭐'s. We will visit again when in town
It's a dive bar, good food, good prices IF you are a local, and it's a good spot to get a late drink. But damn...the aroma is much
Good food and good drinks

Wow. This food is phenomenal! I'm really enjoying my red beans and rice! I might come back tomorrow to try the muffuletta (or maybe just more beans...). Definitely a dive bar so don't come here if you're not comfortable with that.

Great lil dive for after work. I like the staff and choice of beers. The one thing I recommend to the owners is turn the treble down on your speakers. I don't sit inside because it's sharp on my ears, but I do love the tables curbside.
Bartender was great along with the food!
Customers appreciation day was awesome
Crab claws were amazing!
A small dive with some of the best gumbo in town.
Great place for a casual drink to start the evening

My first time here I loved it. I went recently and did not like the vibe at all. I believe we were over charged for our drinks as well. A neighborhood bar but not too friendly. Didn't feel welcomed at all. But that first visit just seemed so perfect. Bummer

Stopped in for some lunch and had the red beans & rice plus a side of sausage. The bartender was very attentive and friendly, and the food was fantastic. Would definitely come back and try more from the menu.
Great food
Simple unassuming New Orleans bar, cool place to hang out and have a beer and a burger.
Great local pub
They have AMAZING bacon cheeseburgers and fries! We absolutely loved the food there!
Good food and drinks if you want something fast.
Love the roast beef poboy!
Love it! Offers a unique feel to New Orleans if you’re looking for a bar to visit or just looking for a bar in general! Is a little small but the bartender is SUPER nice!
Cheap food, cheap beer, excellent place to stop for an amazing lunch. I recommend the alligator po boy. It was unreal!!!
Awesome local tavern.
Best chicken po boy. Great dive.
Great service, wide selection of beer
Excellent lunch

Ate here on our last night in N.O.   Super great local bar.  There were four of us, and I think we tried everything.   The crab claws are amazing.  The red beans and rice were the best I had in N.O  and the gumbo was awesome. Lindsey the bartender was super.  Hard working and very friendly. Caint wait to get back there soon, so I can pick music with "Diddy".
Great hamburgers and friendly bar tenders
Super chill, hole in the wall. Friendly and quick service. Had catfish po'boy 👌
Large Portions, Small Bar
Good food. Quick service.
Great late night drinking spot.  Younger crowd.

I have been to New Orleans many time and have passed over this little jem of a restaurant nested right off canal st. But I must say the food was great better then some larger chain restaurants I have been too. I will say dont go in thinking you can just sit anywhere it's small inside and the bar take up most of the space but there is a few seats, trust me when I say few and it look like you may have stepped back in time a couple of years with nothing inside looks new or remodeled. So I took mine to go i ordered a alligator sausage po-boy, I have have alligator many places ,many ways and I will say this was one of my best. So if your every in town stop by and try it for yourself.
Delicious poboys and jambalaya! Fantastic sweet potato fries and nice and crispy French fries.
Excellent food and fast friendly service
Waited a while before anyone even greeted me.

Awesome dive spot! Cool local daytime crowd and awesome drink prices. We watched AAF on TV and everyone was having a great time. Boudin Balls were on point! Tiny bathrooms so if you are a little larger of a person....good luck.

Great value and really great food.  Had the oyster po boy and it was delicious.  Had draft beer which comes in a clear solo cup but great price.  Nothing fancy, just great staff and great food.  Wonderful value!
What a great way to start our New Orleans adventure. Cheap food but loads of it! Definitely recommend 👌🏼
A PERFECT dive!!!
Gumbo was phenomenal and it's a no nonsense local bar in the middle of the business district
Convenient location, great food, reasonable price

I love this place for the darn good prices. I usually hang outside the establishment though because I'm an elderly 32 year old and it's too loud inside. If I can offer one bit of advice, turn the treble down.
Great little place.
Nice bar where the locals frequent. Good hand poured drinks. Does have food menu. Good sandwiches.
Always a good time when I go....
Delicious food
Delicious gumbo

Good local hangout with cheap drinks. I was surprised by how good the food is. It's a bar with bar style food service (baskets) and mostly fried stuff, but it's good.  The staff and the regulars are helpful and friendly. Great divey spot.
Food was good, but the bathroom was a horror show.
Excellent food and staff.
Nothing great. Dive bar not so cheap.
Thanks Mike for the great food and service. Would recommend to anyone who wants to try some great authentic cajun food.

Great off the path location, design, and decor. The Bartender was extremely knowledgeable in all things New Orleans-whether it be the food, drinks, locations, and tourist traps. You can tell the quality of the bartender and location by how they recommend other locations and direct competitors.  The other customers were great and well receptive as well. Overall a 5+!
Wings were fire!! Love Josh and Brent.

Cool place. Good food. Laid back. Bartender was awesome and gave lots if great tip on what to see and do on our visit. We will definitely stop here anytime we are in town. Folks hanging out here were cool too. Didn't get a change to try the crab claws so we will be back for that.
Great food, large portions, cheap price. Small place and easy to miss, but absolutely recommend

All the fru fru tourists that give this place bad reviews need to be banned from this app. Cajun Mike's is a magical place that we should all feel blessed to experience. Great drinks, great bartenders, great food, great jukebox. Should be a staple for any downtown dweller.
Dive

We had a groupon and decided to try it out.  First of all it is small but don't let that stop you.  It was a Sunday and the place was packed watching football.  Service was excellent food and atmosphere was great. Large servings as well
First restaurant we visited while we were in New Orleans. Great customer service and very tasty food items. It was my first time to ever have an alligator sausage. Must try!

Excellent divey bar. Food is cheap and very nice. Cold beer. And they have Yuenglang!!
Great wings.
Best wings, great little local place.
We were told by a local that this was the place to go and they were right. Best wings ever had. The drinks were free poured and the prices can't be beat. This is a must stop, best hidden gem
Great little place.
Food was delicious, bartenders were a mess but entertaining. Would visit again.
Good food, great service.

I ordered some items from this resturant on doordash before closing time however the restaurant stated they were closed. If you are not going to fullfil orders until the actual closing time then don't offer the delivery service for that time.
Great bar. Excellent food and service.

This was the first place we stopped to eat and it was so good we came here twice! The bartenders are super sweet and so are the guys that work there. The only thing I would change is to not have customers brushing their hair at the bar, but as far as food and service go, it’s awesome.

Just stopped by to grab something to eat. Its a small Pub and we got a Po boy, because the barkeeper recommandet it! It was very Tasty and reasonably priced (~12$ for food + one drink).. Totally worth stopping by if you just want something to eat or a small pub to enjoy a drink...
Great experience! The alligator sausage poboy is awesome
Cheap drinks, cool bartenders and not too far out of the way. What more can you ask for?
Good burgers
Excellent place to have a couples off beers and sandwiches.
Good Creole food. Large portions, very reasonable pricing. Bar tender was very nice. Music was quite loud but good genre of music. Decor was comfortable dive bar motif. Felt welcomed.
Good bartenders and nice folks.
Good boy at a good bar
Good food, ok service, the bartender said sorry I was focused on the locals,  not a bad thing just thought maybe we would get food a bit quicker than we did.
Fun little hole in the wall. Great beer selection. Friendly service!

Stopped here for a lunch and everything was nice, quick, and delicious. Clean place with good atmosphere. Good fair prices, very friendly staff. Fantastic sweet potato fries! Jambalaya was huge so best to split with someone.
Place is so small, the food was not that good but the service was good.
Great people. Excellent food. Excellent bartenders!

This place is disgusting! A cockroach crawled all over the bar infront of me and the bartender wasn't suprised nor seemed to care. She said, "Was it big? It's New Orleans, there are bugs." Obviously, there are bugs. But bugs in a resturant says a lot. Let alone the workers reaction. We didn't receive any kind of discount. The food was good but who knows what is IN the food or had touched it.
Awesome great come again thanks!!!!!
Service was good, food left something to be desired. Not authentic New Orleans
We really like the food and prices.
Love this place! (when you can get a bar stool). Good drinks and pub grub at very reasonable prices! Nice staff as well!
Nate is one of the best bartenders in the city
Great place for legitimate, good food and a good authentic New Orleans atmosphere. You have to look for it and know its here but worth the walk and the stop. Would recommend anytime.
Cold beer and DAMN good shrimp poyboys.
Cozy little hole in the wall bar serving up a good shrimp po'boy and cold beer...Check groupon for a meal deal..
Great lunch shared with husband.  He got red beans and rice, and I got a shrimp basket.  What a feast! Friendly service too!
I love Nate 's Virgin Bloody Marys.
Great food and service
Great food! Freshly made to order.
Great food. Friendly bar.
Best Red Beans and Rice ever!
Fun little place with the locals. Good food.
No frills place. Had the cochon au lait and loved it.
Best priced restaurant we went to the whole week we were in New orleans. Very nice people very good drinks and awesome food. Hands down the best place to stop in to grab a bit.
Eat here. Seriously, go get a whole bowl of crab n butter and chow down. Well worth the 8 bucks. Gator po boy was awesome as well.
Loved the remodel. Got a groupon and am glad I found this spot!
Best dive in New Orleans!!

This was the First and last place we ate while me and my boyfriend were visiting new Orleans for the first time ever! When we first got into downtown we had literally just gotten off the plane, were hungry and felt super jet lagged! And mikes was the best hole in the wall ! Best Po Boy I've ever ate in my life! That alligator sausage is to die for!! I'd fly all the way back just to get some of that gator!!! This pub is the reason I will most definitely be returning to NOLA! It's now become our tradition to always eat here first while in new Orleans! Highly recommended! you won't be disappointed! If I could give 10 stars I would !
Best gumbo I’ve had in NO.  Bartender is awesome!

Great bartender, great music (because of bartender), food on point. When my girlfriend and I walked up at first we were a bit.. intimidated I guess. But that was washed away almost immediately after walking in
Bartender was the bomb she took care of everyone thoughtfully. Po boys were fresh!
Great locals dive bar.
Really enjoyed the food. Had the onion rings but all my friends enjoyed their Po Boys.
Quaint bar with great food and service!
Amazing roast pork po boy!
Poboys were good. Crowded.

Without question, the best $10 I've ever spent on a simple meal while traveling on business. The previous night, I ordered room service at my hotel...that too was a simple meal, but a very different cost ($45). Big mistake. Yuge mistake. Consider this my 2 thumbs up along with a hi-five and a handshake to the establishment and it's employees.
Cool neighborhood hangout.
Love this place. Great staff and food. Both is a must Mahalo
Without a doubt hands down the best Po Boys in New Orleans

Absolute gem if you run across it.  It was acriss from our hotel, and we wanted something quick and easy .  Saw this place and said "what the heck".  From outside,  it's very simple.  Inside is a step ir two above a "dive bar".  But don't let that fool you, it's an incredible place!  Service...really couldn't get any better.  And they are super friendly.  Atmosphere, other customers, just the general feel of the place was very good.  Now the food. :-)   Of course this was just one sampling, but I have no reason to believe the rest of the menu is any different.  I had the Red Beans and Rice and the oyster Po-Boy (no, I didn't finish it all).  Absolutely incredible!  Oysters were fried perfectly, and the overall flavor balance...delicious!  And a plus, they load on so many oysters, you literally cannot keep them on the sandwich and still eat it.  The red beans also excellent,  and per my wife, the muffelatta and sweet potato fries were just as good.  Adult beverages are quite good.  Many varieties of everything, including their bourbon selection (my personal favorite).  Give it a try, you won't be disappointed .

Classic hole-in-the-wall dive bar! We stopped in after our arrival in NOLA to kill time while waiting for our check-in time. I tried a hot roast beef po boy and he had a cochon de lait po boy. They were both phenomenal! And, despite CLEARLY being tourists (luggage in tow...) the bartender made us feel welcome.
It was a pretty good place would have maybe like a little better food

Bars like this don't exist anymore. They'd copy this bar for television shows and name it 'The Local'. This is an absolutely no frills joint with good sandwiches, a decent liquor selection, a few taps, and honest to goodness service from real people. Don't come here for wows. Come here for a slice of Americana. Come here to be yourself and watch others be themselves. Chat with the guy next to you. Or don't. Show up drunk. Or don't. Get drunk. Or don't. Stop in for a bite, or stay all day. No expectations. You do you.  Oh, and get the Cochon and whatever beer they have in a glass. You're welcome.
Friendly staff and amazing food. Best place for late night eats
SOOOOOOOO YUMMY! Great poboys and friendly staff. Came just in time before their renovations. Can’t wait to see after! EXTREMELY AFFORDABLE!
Best bar in New Orleans. Lol
Great bartenders and good food...They have a jukebox here with almost any song. Try the sampler here, its got the most variety for your buck
Great food. It doesn’t look like much but they can churn out some good po boys. Prices are very reasonable; for under $30, we walked back to the hotel full and stumbling.
Favorite hang out spot
Standard sports bar, with great local food. We enjoyed the shrimp, boudin balls and gumbo. Great if you need a quick bite to eat before hitting Bourbon street!!
Food was okay.  Bartenders were nice. Beer was good.
Great, fresh sandwiches and friendly service.
Hidden secret!! Sports  Bar & PBR draft
Downtown hole in the wall!
The cheese burger & sweet potato fries were delicious. Great lunch spot.
The Thursday night bartender is drunk, belligerent, and unacceptably unprofessional. Unfortunate, because the food was amazing.
Good bar away from the hustle and bustle. Great drinks and food
If you're a hipster with masochistic tendencies and a high tolerance to salmonella, this is your place
This is a "go to" spot. Great good, drinks and prices. A lot of value. Staff has always been great too!
Great bar that's small and nice to relax from the hustle and bussle.
Great gumbo, best bloody Mary I ever had.
Good po' boys, cheap beer, entertaining staff! Glad I stopped here.
Great place and great people
Been coming here for years....the Bloody Mary's are awesome.
Good spot for after work drink. GREAT BARTENDERS.....AND GOOD COLD BEER....
First place I stopped to eat at in NOLA, nice atmosphere, the staff was decent. But have to say the food was not that great.
Very dirty. I ordered 3 drinks and they all had left over "labels" in them! I asked for a new drink several times and every time there were "things" flowing in my drink.

Best Dive Bar between Downtown and Uptown. Genuine good people, and Super Awesome Bartenders. Usually start the night here or end it. Decent Food for a quick bite, or something to counter the drinkin'.

Sasha is absolutely amazing. We road tripped down from Wisconsin. Just arrived, and rolled into the bar randomly while waiting to check in to our room. She is nothing but smiles and helpfulness. Giving us all the details on what we should check out before we leave (wrote it down on paper for us too!) Such a great first experience in this city. I wish she could just clock out, and come explore with us!

Sasha is the best. If she had a nickname it would be Sasha the machine....because she rocks socks and has no imperfections. She gave us a list of places to visit while here on vacation in New Orleans. Her skill for tequila shots is on par and is uncontested. If you're in town stop by and get a drink, preferably with Sasha!!!!
Great simple place off the main street. Had a pork po boy, 😋
One of my favorite bars in New Orleans.Close enough to the action,but  out of the way enough to relax and have a good time.

Worse bar experience ever. Bad service, horrible food, and the rudest bartender that I've met in NOLA! If you fancy yourself a respectable person do not waist your money at Cajun mike's. There are many more wonderful places to patronize.
Fun little pub
Hot bartender

Cajun Mike's is a reliable dive bar, getting filthier by the year. If they have food, don't eat  it. Often the door will be open in the oppressive heat, rendering the AC useless, as the bartender believes it will attract patrons.  Can't beat $2-3 beer, though!
Good lunch spot.

Went in the other night and the female bartender was so drunk she couldn't even pour a beer, myself and 2 other customers walked out after waiting 15 minutes for a drink in a completely empty bar after the bartender said it would be "A while"
Very good Cuban sandwich, friendly bartender and cold beer.

Great bartender, great location if walking, and good food. We dropped by because we had a Groupon for $20 worth of food. It was good food, just not fantastic. The bartender made good conversation. Overall, good lunch!

Sat at the bar got 2 beers watched 3 6+ tops walk out due to bad service of the bartender chance had an self put attitude never greeted a table. I could understand bad service but I would have walked out too 1/2 star at that.
Bloody Mary's are legit !!
Great little dive bar that has some excellent combo baskets!!!

It was Monday and the bartender made her nut before I got there, because of a concert, so she only took care of regulars until there was there no one left except me. Hopefully the kitchen staff, who got served, before me helps pay her rent.
Fresh and delicious catfish, it's my Friday spot after 12pm Mass. Especially since it's s couple of doors from the church.

I found this place while roaming around canal street, New Orleans. It was a good found. Its a small local drink+food joint and very cheap compared to other places. They don't have much space inside, nor they have live music. But if you are tired and need to wet your throat for a couple beer with couple of friends, you got this place. They don't have table larger for more than three people, so watch out and lose some losers.  The service was fantastic. I went in the morning, the gentleman in the bar himself stepped out and took my order and explained everything. And there was another guy, who came out right out of the kitchen and served food and then went inside again. OMG, was he the chef himself?  I tried alligator sausage 🐊 po'boy and it was super delicious. It was my first alligator and I was quite skeptical about it. My heart stopped pounding after I took the first bite, was it that good or they made it that good or was it because of first time experience. Doesn't matter, I enjoyed till my last bite. Only the bread 🍞 was too hard to bite sometimes. And lots of fries would make you regret later. You get free refills if you buy soft drinks. And all of these for just $14. Also watch out for the check in offer.  I'd definitely recommend everyone to check them out if you are in NOLA.
Dive bar and cheap for New Orlean. If you want to take a breather from bourbon this is a good place to stop by and grab a pbr.

Absolutely TERRIBLE service. Sat down at a mostly empty bar (my friend and I at the bar, maybe 5 other people as well) thinking we'd get quick service. The bartender took my friend's food order, then she walked away without taking mine. The bartender then proceeded to ignore me for half an hour, even after bringing my friend's app. Had to leave this place and go elsewhere for food. Thanks for making your customers feel unwanted.
Food was great (tried the alligator sausage po boy and gumbo), staff was friendly, and the drinks were good.
Everything looks old and worn out inside and the old TV's don't have clear pictures - not good to watch any games. I liked the bartender but that's about it
Perfect dive bar for when you don't want to pay 9$ for a domestic beer
Friendly
Always a fun time

Best CBD dive. Frequented by tourists and regulars alike. Tasty bar food. Get the cochon de lait or alligator sausage poboy--they're my favourites. Half order of fries or onion rings are awesome to snack on while knocking 'em back.  Happy hour from 11am-7pm daily. Awesome bartenders. Several TVs inside and two facing outside for those smoking outdoors.  Specials during Saints and LSU games.

My girlfriend and I were walking around trying to find something to eat after traveling to New Orleans for the Essence Festival. We usually reserve a table using the OpenTable app and read reveiws prior to going to a restaurant. However, it was late and most of the high-end, good restaurants closed early on a Thursday night. We came across Cajun Mikes and decided to give it try. We found a table and I tried to get the bartender's attention, but she was extremely rude! She (the bartender) was hugged up on one guy and talking to another guy at the bar. She didn't think to stop what she was doing with these guys and provide us service. I tried to get her attention several times even after she looked me dead in my eyes and walked pass me three times!!! She had extremely piss poor customer service and should probably reconsider her profession. We walked out! I would never visit this establishment again! Customer service is everything, and reading the other reviews after the fact, I am glad we didn't eat here.
